      <h1 class='title'>Public Services (Co-payments)</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 cc110-1WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_111ws' title='Col. 111WS &mdash; HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 c111WS' name='column_111ws' href='#column_111ws' rel='bookmark'>111WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-05286'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_568'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-angela-eagle' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_568' title='Link to this speech by Ms Angela Eagle' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-angela-eagle" title="Ms Angela Eagle">Angela Eagle</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-05286">To ask the Deputy Prime Minister what plans he has to introduce co-payments for the public services for which he is responsible. [102201]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-05287'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_569'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-nick-raynsford' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_569' title='Link to this speech by Mr Nick Raynsford' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-nick-raynsford" title="Mr Nick Raynsford">Mr. Raynsford</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-05287">The Office of the Deputy Prime Minister aims to deliver high quality public services in the most cost-effective way. The Office of the Deputy Prime Minister currently has PFI projects that deliver investment in affordable housing, fire stations and joint service centres. The Office of the Deputy Prime Minister will continue to consider PPPs and PFIs where they minimise financial risk and maxirnise benefit to the public.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
